    "V1 (Infrastructure implementation): Quantum communication networks in a 6G environment demand a specialized infrastructure that differs from traditional communication networks (Akyildiz et al. 2020).",
    "Quantum repeaters are crucial components needed to strengthen and transmit quantum signals over long distances, ensuring the integrity and quality of quantum information (Awschalom et al. 2021).",
    "However, implementing such a widespread infrastructure presents significant challenges (Awschalom et al. 2021).",
    "Firstly, the cost of deploying and maintaining quantum repeaters and associated equipment is high.",
    "Additionally, the complexity of these systems, including the need for precise control and synchronization, adds to the implementation challenges (Urgelles et al. 2022)."
